  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is a control matched prospective study evaluating the use of seromuscular flap for high
      risk anastomoses.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      30 eligible patients have been enrolled in the study then each case was matched to a control
      of patients who undwerwent resection anastomosis with primary anastomosis only in the same
      study period in terms of age, gender, comorbidity, diagnosis.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
